The Industrial Bank of Japan &lt;IBJT.T> (IBJ)amortized 68 billion yen worth of loans, including thewrite-off of an unspecified amount of loans, to the &lt;Japan LineLtd> group in the year ended March 31, an IBJ spokesman said.    He declined to comment on a report in the economic dailyNihon Keizai Shimbun that it had written off loans worth 15billion yen to Japan Line, one of the world's largest tankeroperators.    Japan Line's current liabilities amounted to 68.98 billionyen at the end of September.    In December, Japan Line asked its creditor banks to shelverepayment of 124 billion yen of outstanding loans and about 153billion in loans to its subsidiaries following the yen's steeprise and the world recession in shipping. REUTER&#3;